    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-07-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-07-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="404"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d404">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">756D.5–MAP/7–2551: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Indonesia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cochran</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Djakarta</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-07-25">July 25,
                            1951—noon.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>127. <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 97, July 21.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d404fn1">In telegram 97 to Djakarta, July 21, the Department of
                        State asked Ambassador Cochran if he thought it propitious to approach the
                        Indonesian Government about the publication of the <gloss target="#t_MDAP1"
                            >MDAP</gloss> accord negotiated in August, 1950
                        (756D.5–MAP/3–2051).</note> Evening twenty-fourth discussed with Vice Pres
                    Hatta question publishing and registering with <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_MDAP1">MDAP</gloss> agreement which I negotiated with Hatta. I
                    pointed out only limited comment had been aroused <gloss target="#t_Indo1"
                        >Indo</gloss> by statement Pres Truman June 25 reporting <gloss
                        target="#t_MDAP1">MDAP</gloss> in Far East including summary aid given
                        <gloss target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss> police constabulary. Hatta agreeable
                    to Dept’s request on understanding I would also consult <gloss target="#t_SYG1"
                        >SYG</gloss> Darmasetiawan of <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> who
                    was familiar with negotiation agreement and now in responsible position to pass
                    on question at issue.</p>
                <p>Saw Darmasetiawan last night. He said <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss>
                    agreeable initiation <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> registration and
                    publishing agreement. He feared, however, that publishing agreement by itself
                    might attract too much attention and arouse leftist criticism within <gloss
                        target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss> just at this time when govt already facing
                    many problems with Parliament. He hoped therefore the publicity on <gloss
                        target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss> could be tied up with story of assistance to
                    Far East as whole. Dept consequently now has <gloss target="#t_Indo1"
                        >Indo</gloss> approval to request contained <gloss target="#t_Deptel1"
                        >Deptel</gloss> 97 but I feel consideration should be given to avoiding more
                    publicity than strictly necessary.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cochran</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
